  "prompt": "What is the job outlook like in the US after getting a MS in electrical engineering?",
  "response": "The job outlook for electrical engineers in the United States is generally positive:\n\n1. Employment Growth\n- The Bureau of Labor Statistics projects about 7% job growth for electrical engineers from 2020-2030\n- This is about as fast as the average for all occupations\n\n2. Median Salary\n- Median annual wage was approximately $100,830 in May 2021\n- Top 10% can earn over $162,930\n\n3. Top Industries Hiring\n- Electronics manufacturing\n- Telecommunications\n- Aerospace and defense\n- Renewable energy\n- Semiconductor design\n- Robotics\n- Medical device technology\n\n4. Emerging Areas\n- Artificial Intelligence\n- Internet of Things (IoT)\n- Electric vehicle technology\n- 5G and telecommunications\n- Renewable energy systems\n\n5. Geographic Hotspots\n- Silicon Valley, California\n- Austin, Texas\n- Boston, Massachusetts\n- Seattle, Washington\n- Research Triangle, North Carolina\n\n6. Additional Advantages\n- With a master's degree, you may have better job prospects\n- Higher starting salaries compared to bachelor's degree holders\n- More opportunities in research and advanced engineering roles\n\nOverall, the field remains robust with diverse opportunities across multiple sectors.",
